Judge Neil Gorsuch has been confirmed by the Senate Judiciary Committee and his nomination will now go to the full Senate for a final vote. Gorsuch is highly qualified and has a strong record of defending the Constitution. He has participated in over 2,700 cases on the 10th Circuit, with 97 percent of them being decided unanimously and he was in the majority 99 percent of the time. Gorsuch has met with nearly 80 Senators, answered hundreds of questions, and sat through nearly 20 hours of questioning by the Senate Judiciary Committee. President Trump nominated Gorsuch to fulfill his promise of appointing a Supreme Court Justice who will uphold and defend the Constitution. Gorsuch has received support from various individuals and organizations for his exemplary service and record. The full Senate will vote to confirm Gorsuch to the Supreme Court this week.